SIMPLE: inhabit
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Inhabit
<hw>In*hab"it</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Inhabited</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Inhabiting</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[OE. <ets>enhabiten</ets>, OF.
<ets>enhabiter</ets>, L. <ets>inhabitare</ets>; pref. <ets>in-</ets> in
+ <ets>habitare</ets> to dwell. See <er>Habit</er>.]</ety> <def>To live
or dwell in; to occupy, as a place of settled residence; <as>as, wild
beasts <ex>inhabit</ex> the forest; men <ex>inhabit</ex> cities and
houses.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The high and lofty One, that <qex>inhabiteth</qex> eternity.</q>
<rj><qau>Is. lvii. 15.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>O, who would <qex>inhabit</qex>⟦br⟧
This bleak world alone?</q> <rj><qau>Moore.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Inhabit</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Inhabit
<hw>In*hab"it</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To have residence in a place;
to dwell; to live; to abide.</def> <mark>[Archaic or Poetic]</mark>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>They say wild beasts <qex>inhabit</qex> here.</q>
<rj><qau>Waller.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Inhabitable</ent>⟦br⟧
